<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="1068" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,639,486,1730]" lastBlockId="2.[685,1173,194,1191]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[175,298,673,694]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[310,398,673,694]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Holotype</typeStatus>
male. Length 
<quantity box="[553,634,673,694]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068" unit="mm" value="3.9">3.9 mm</quantity>
, width across humeri 
<quantity box="[344,418,699,720]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
. Body form moderately convex and glabrous dorsally. Head and pronotum dark green and shiny, elytra darker, striae with green reflections, legs reddish brown; clypeus and frons slightly microreticulated (
<figureCitation box="[404,463,805,826]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[197,236,1439,1458]" captionTargetBox="[185,1187,197,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-99@3.[175,1190,194,1423]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 1–7. Canthidium kohlmanni, holotype. 1–2) Habitus, dorsal and ventral views, respectively; 3) Head;" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[488,549,805,826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Head:</emphasis>
Clypeus slightly concave, apex bidentate, median emargination V-shaped, rugose-punctate anteriorly, transversally reticulated posteriorly; frons almost flat with 2 barely visible swellings, punctures confluent, sparser and shallower toward vertex; vertex slightly convex, almost impunctate on each side of midline. Eyes very narrow, with 2 facets at posterior end of genae; eyes separated by about 9–10 times maximum width of eye (
<figureCitation box="[372,436,1045,1066]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[197,236,1439,1458]" captionTargetBox="[185,1187,197,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-99@3.[175,1190,194,1423]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 1–7. Canthidium kohlmanni, holotype. 1–2) Habitus, dorsal and ventral views, respectively; 3) Head;" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Antennae reddish brown, sericeous. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[332,444,1071,1092]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Pronotum:</emphasis>
Surface shiny, uniformly punctate; punctures sparse, shallow, minute to small at sides, like those on vertex (
<figureCitation box="[561,622,1124,1145]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[197,236,1439,1458]" captionTargetBox="[185,1187,197,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-99@3.[175,1190,194,1423]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 1–7. Canthidium kohlmanni, holotype. 1–2) Habitus, dorsal and ventral views, respectively; 3) Head;" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); lateral fovea semicircular and slightly marked; posterior margin lacking elongate punctures or groove. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[230,300,1204,1225]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Elytra:</emphasis>
Striae moderately impressed, interrupted by annulated punctures separated by about 2–3 diameters of 1 puncture; intervals very finely punctate, surface shiny (
<figureCitation box="[390,449,1284,1305]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[197,236,1439,1458]" captionTargetBox="[185,1187,197,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-99@3.[175,1190,194,1423]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 1–7. Canthidium kohlmanni, holotype. 1–2) Habitus, dorsal and ventral views, respectively; 3) Head;" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[473,544,1284,1305]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Wings:</emphasis>
Macropterous, wings functional. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[410,486,1310,1331]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Venter:</emphasis>
Proepisternum excavate anteriorly, surface microreticulated; sternellum smooth and with a line of setiferous punctures along base; mesosternum microreticulated with minute punctures; metasternum with minute punctures denser than mesosternum (
<figureCitation box="[456,515,1443,1464]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[197,236,1439,1458]" captionTargetBox="[185,1187,197,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-99@3.[175,1190,194,1423]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 1–7. Canthidium kohlmanni, holotype. 1–2) Habitus, dorsal and ventral views, respectively; 3) Head;" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[533,637,1443,1464]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Abdomen:</emphasis>
Sternites 1–6 microreticulated, with minute punctures; pygidium convex, shiny, with minute, shallow punctures (
<figureCitation box="[255,314,1523,1544]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[197,236,1439,1458]" captionTargetBox="[185,1187,197,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-99@3.[175,1190,194,1423]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 1–7. Canthidium kohlmanni, holotype. 1–2) Habitus, dorsal and ventral views, respectively; 3) Head;" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[332,386,1523,1544]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Legs:</emphasis>
Protibia with 3 large teeth on external border, apical and middle teeth separated by 2 denticles, inner apical margin of protibia produced into triangular anterior projection and slightly bent downwards; apical spur simple and slightly curved inward (
<figureCitation box="[300,359,1656,1677]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[197,236,1439,1458]" captionTargetBox="[185,1187,197,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-99@3.[175,1190,194,1423]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 1–7. Canthidium kohlmanni, holotype. 1–2) Habitus, dorsal and ventral views, respectively; 3) Head;" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); profemora microreticulated; meso- and metafemora densely punctate, punctures minute, shallow, denser apically. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[441,541,1709,1730]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Aedeagus:</emphasis>
Parameres moderately short, apices truncated to slightly rounded, inner margins slightly concave (
<figureCitation box="[979,1067,220,242]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[197,236,1439,1458]" captionTargetBox="[185,1187,197,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-99@3.[175,1190,194,1423]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 1–7. Canthidium kohlmanni, holotype. 1–2) Habitus, dorsal and ventral views, respectively; 3) Head;" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Figs. 5–7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="1068" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[685,1173,194,1191]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,824,247,268]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Etymology.</emphasis>
We dedicate this species to Bert Kohlmann, friend and specialist of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[685,812,301,322]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Scarabaeinae">Scarabaeinae</taxonomicName>
, and author of the works on the species of 
<taxonomicName box="[710,822,327,349]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[710,822,327,349]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Canthidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from North America and 
<collectingCountry box="[1063,1168,328,349]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[685,1173,194,1191]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,932,354,375]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Taxonomic Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is distinguished by the following combination of characters: body moderately convex; dorsally dark green in color, pronotum and head with a light cast green and reddish; head with rounded swellings, not tuberculate; vertex slightly punctate; eye dorsally with two facets wide at the posterior end of gena, interocular distance separated by about 9–10 times the width of an eye; antennal club reddish brown and sericeous; pronotal surface with shallow and minute punctures on disc, at sides with punctures moderate in size; basal pronotal border not margined; elytra with eight clearly punctate striae; mesosternum with minute punctures; abdominal sternites shagreened, pygidium smooth and with minute, shallow punctures; macropterous; and the shape of the parameres (
<figureCitation box="[923,1016,789,811]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[197,236,1439,1458]" captionTargetBox="[185,1187,197,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-99@3.[175,1190,194,1423]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 1–7. Canthidium kohlmanni, holotype. 1–2) Habitus, dorsal and ventral views, respectively; 3) Head;" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Figs. 5–7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[685,1173,194,1191]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">
<taxonomicName box="[709,929,815,837]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kohlmanni">
<emphasis box="[709,929,815,837]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Canthidium kohlmanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kohlmann" authorityName="Kohlmann" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudoperceptibile">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Canthidium pseudoperceptibile</emphasis>
Kohlmann
</taxonomicName>
and Sol´ıs (the new species was compared with 
<typeStatus box="[961,1052,871,892]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">paratypes</typeStatus>
of this species), but it is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudoperceptibile">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">C. pseudoperceptibile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the frons and vertex with denser and shallower punctures (
<figureCitation box="[888,945,952,973]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[197,236,1439,1458]" captionTargetBox="[185,1187,197,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-99@3.[175,1190,194,1423]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 1–7. Canthidium kohlmanni, holotype. 1–2) Habitus, dorsal and ventral views, respectively; 3) Head;" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
<emphasis box="[952,1011,952,973]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">versus</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[1019,1077,952,973]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[175,214,1310,1329]" captionTargetBox="[157,1166,196,1278]" captionTargetId="figure-195@4.[154,1169,194,1294]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 8–12. Canthidium pseudoperceptibile, male paratype. 8) Habitus, dorsal view; 9) Head; 10) Protibia; 11–12) Parameres, caudal and lateral views, respectively." pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
), the pronotum with finer and shallower punctation (
<figureCitation box="[1113,1172,980,1001]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[197,236,1439,1458]" captionTargetBox="[185,1187,197,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-99@3.[175,1190,194,1423]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 1–7. Canthidium kohlmanni, holotype. 1–2) Habitus, dorsal and ventral views, respectively; 3) Head;" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
<emphasis box="[685,744,1007,1028]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">versus</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[749,804,1007,1028]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[175,214,1310,1329]" captionTargetBox="[157,1166,196,1278]" captionTargetId="figure-195@4.[154,1169,194,1294]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 8–12. Canthidium pseudoperceptibile, male paratype. 8) Habitus, dorsal view; 9) Head; 10) Protibia; 11–12) Parameres, caudal and lateral views, respectively." pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
), the protibia with the apical and middle teeth separated by denticles (
<figureCitation box="[959,1016,1034,1055]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[197,236,1439,1458]" captionTargetBox="[185,1187,197,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-99@3.[175,1190,194,1423]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 1–7. Canthidium kohlmanni, holotype. 1–2) Habitus, dorsal and ventral views, respectively; 3) Head;" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
<emphasis box="[1024,1083,1034,1055]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">versus</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[1090,1160,1034,1055]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[175,214,1310,1329]" captionTargetBox="[157,1166,196,1278]" captionTargetId="figure-195@4.[154,1169,194,1294]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 8–12. Canthidium pseudoperceptibile, male paratype. 8) Habitus, dorsal view; 9) Head; 10) Protibia; 11–12) Parameres, caudal and lateral views, respectively." pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
), and the shape of the parameres of the male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[692,782,1088,1110]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[197,236,1439,1458]" captionTargetBox="[185,1187,197,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-99@3.[175,1190,194,1423]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 1–7. Canthidium kohlmanni, holotype. 1–2) Habitus, dorsal and ventral views, respectively; 3) Head;" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Figs. 5–7</figureCitation>
versus 
<figureCitation box="[856,969,1088,1110]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[175,214,1310,1329]" captionTargetBox="[157,1166,196,1278]" captionTargetId="figure-195@4.[154,1169,194,1294]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 8–12. Canthidium pseudoperceptibile, male paratype. 8) Habitus, dorsal view; 9) Head; 10) Protibia; 11–12) Parameres, caudal and lateral views, respectively." pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">Figs. 11–12</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[685,1173,194,1191]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">
To include 
<taxonomicName box="[825,957,1114,1136]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kohlmanni">
<emphasis box="[825,957,1114,1136]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1068">C. kohlmanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we propose the following modifications in Moctezuma 
